genresAdvancedInfo.name: djembe
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Djembe is a West African drumming tradition that originated in Mali and Guinea. It features a large, goblet-shaped drum that is played with bare hands. Djembe music is known for its energetic rhythms and complex polyrhythms, which are created by layering different drumming patterns on top of each other. It is often used in traditional West African ceremonies and celebrations, as well as in modern music genres such as world music and fusion jazz.
